  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study examines pain-related evoked potentials (PREP) in patients with peripheral nerve
      injuries. Since previous studies found altered latencies and amplitudes of PREP in
      generalized polyneuropathies, e. g. HIV-polyneuropathy and fibromyalgia, this study
      investigates if these alterations are detectable in unilateral peripheral nerve injuries as
      well.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
